      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>T. Mitchell Prudden graduated from the Sheffield Scientific School, Yale, in 1872 and received his M. D. from Yale School of Medicine in 1875. He became an assistant (1879) and was professor of pathology (1892-1909) in the College of Physicians and Surgeons, Columbia University. In 1901 he was made a director of the Rockefeller Institute for medical research.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>T. Mitchell Prudden's archives notably include numerous slides of western Native American sites.</p>  
